63. find a solution to a system of equations
      Returns a solution to a system of equations, or element-wise across a collection of systems of equations.
      Syntax: x = solvep({Equations},{Variables})
      Allowed types for x: qubit, cbit, qnum, qnump, cnum, qstr, qstrs, qstrc, qstre, cstr, cstrs, ctrc, cstre, matrix, block, circ, list, dict, set, map, gate, struct. 
      Allowed types for Equations: A list or set of strings containing equations written according to this documentation, or one such equation as a string. A collection of such lists or sets for element-wise solving.
      Allowed types for Variables: A list or set of strings containing all of the well-defined variables appearing in the equations, or one such variable as a string. A collection of such lists or sets for element-wise solving.
      Examples:

      x = solvep({"x+1=10"},{"x"}) = solvep("x+1=10","x") = 9 = "x=9" = {"x=9"}
      x = solvep({"x+1=y","y*x=90"},{"x","y"}) = solvep({"x+1=y","y*x=90","y+z=10","z=10-y"},{"x","y"}) = {"x=9, y=10"} = "x=9, y=10"
      x = solvep({"x^2 - 5*x + 6 = 0"},{"x"}) = {"x=2" or "x=3"} = "x=2" or "x=3"
      x = solvep({"x^2 + y^2 = 25", "x + y = 7"},{"x","y"}) = {"x=3, y=4" or "x=4, y=3"} = "x=3, y=4" or "x=4, y=3"

