65. Difference operator
      Returns an output detailing how two references of the same or comparable types are different. It does so numerical for numerical types, lexographically for string types, and by element for collections.
      Syntax: x = a diff b
      Allowed types for x: qubit, cbit, qnum, qnump, cnum, qstr, qstrs, qstrc, qstre, cstr, cstrs, ctrc, cstre, matrix, block, circ, list, dict, set, map. 
      Allowed types for a & b: any.
      Examples:
      1 diff 2 = 1
      2 diff 1 = -1
      1 diff 1 = 0
      "hi" diff "bye" = 6
      "bye" diff "hi" = -6
      "hi" diff "hi" = 0
      
      {1,2,3} diff {4,5,6} = 0 = {3,3,3} = {1 diff 4, 2 diff 5, 3 diff 6}
      {1,2,3} diff {1,2,3} = 0 = {0,0,0} = {1 diff 1, 2 diff 2, 3 diff 3}
      {1,2,3} diff {1,2,3,4} = 1 = {"0","0","0","n4"} = {"1 diff 1", "2 diff 2", "3 diff 3", n"0 diff 4"}
      {1,2,3} diff {4,5,6,7,8} = 2 = {"3","3","3","n7","n8"} = {"1 diff 4", "2 diff 5", "3 diff 6", n"0 diff 7", n"0 diff 8"}
      
      
