	A statement that executes a block of code, if the expression it is evaluating is true. Includes an optional 'else', and 'else if' which allows you to specify code to execute if the expression is false.
	it also does return a boolean (it is optional to save this value), based on whether if statement executed or not.
	Syntax: 
			a = if(Expression){
				 ...
			} 
			b = else if (Expression) {
			    ...
			} 
			c = else {
				...
			}
		or
			if(Expression){
				 ...
			} 
			else if (Expression) {
			    ...
			} 
			else {
				...
			}
	Allowed types for a,b,c, & Expression: any (bitwise 0 will evaluate to false, anything else to true)


